# zip: the TOTAL Zip. Per SEQ row, two inner lists of equal length zip into Ok (a List<(X,Y)>);
# a length-mismatched row lands in Err carrying its two inner lists. Here element e gives lhs [0..e)
# and rhs [0..e+(e&1)) — so even e zips (Ok) and odd e mismatches (Err). The clean `zip` needs the
# size pass to prove the inner bounds agree; zip handles ragged pairs with no proof.
# n = 4
# = Sum tags=[1] [⊥, ()x1]
input iota map (x -> (x iota, (x, x and 1) add iota) zip)
